'''Ubaihōmei Shrine''' (うばいほうめいじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Hachijō|Q1354815|WD=Q1354815|1=Hachijō, Tokyo}} ({{ill|lt=Hachijō-jima|Q1191120|WD=Q1191120|1=Hachijō-jima}}), {{ill|lt=Tokyo|Q1490|WD=Q1490|1=Tokyo}}. It is the general tutelary shrine of Hachijō-jima and {{ill|lt=Aogashima|Q615578|WD=Q615578|1=Aogashima}}.

It was formed by merging the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} '''Ubainomikoto Shrine''' (うばいのみことじんじゃ) and '''Koshikinomikoto Shrine''' (こしきのみことじんじゃ). Its current name combines the names of the deities of those two shrines, described below<ref>[https://ubai-houmei.tokyo/ 優婆夷宝明神社] - official website</ref><ref name="yafune">[http://www.yafune.server-shared.com/you-xu/ 由緒] - Yafune Shrine</ref>.

=== Enshrined deities ===
* Ubai Ōkami (うばいのおおかみ) - one of the eight consorts, Yasoyaehime, of {{ill|UNKNOWN|WD=Q8009611|lt=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|1=Kotoshironushi-no-Mikoto|WD=Q8009611}} (Mishima Daimyōjin)<ref name="jinjacho">[http://www.tokyo-jinjacho.or.jp/tosho/3142/ 優婆夷宝明神社] - Tokyo Association of Shinto Shrines</ref><ref name="jinjacho2">[http://tosho.tokyo-jinjacho.or.jp/hachijyoujima.html 優婆夷宝明神社] - Tokyo Association of Shinto Shrines (Island Special Edition)</ref>; i.e., Ubainomikoto, deity of the Shikinaisha Ubainomikoto Shrine<ref name="yafune"/>.
* Hōmei-no-Kami (ほうめいのかみ) - her child Kohōmaru<ref name="jinjacho"/><ref name="jinjacho2"/>; i.e., Koshikinomikoto, deity of the Shikinaisha Koshikinomikoto Shrine<ref name="yafune"/>.

